         <abstract>
            <p>The $\overset{\circ}{H}^1$-projection into finite element spaces based on quasi-uniform partitions of a bounded smooth domain in $R^N, N \geqslant 2$ arbitrary, is shown to be stable in the maximum norm (or, in the case of piecewise linear or bilinear functions, almost stable). It is not assumed that the mesh-domains coincide with the basic domain.</p>
          </abstract>
